{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857763872,"sessionID":"ses_286a4e46effeEb8MI420VG5SW0","part":{"id":"prt_d795f058a001F3KtM4pFbfGjfy","messageID":"msg_d795bae1f001o3D0XHwfAGUs8t","sessionID":"ses_286a4e46effeEb8MI420VG5SW0","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-21eedac3ccd44317ba0eb274da22374e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md","content":"# AR-013 вҖ” Redis еӯҳеӮЁе®һзҺ° Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-013 вҖ” Redis еӯҳеӮЁе®һзҺ° |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Add Redis client dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/redis/go-redis/v9@latest`\n  - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Add Valkey client dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go@latest`\n  - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Add test dependency (miniredis)\n  - Run: `go get github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2@latest`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy`\n\n- [ ] **T1.4** Verify pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo exists\n  - Check: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` has SandboxInfo struct\n  - Verify struct has required fields: Kind, SandboxID, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, LastActivity\n\n### Phase 2: Core Interface & Types\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/store/doc.go`\n  - Add package documentation\n  - Describe store module purpose (Redis/Valkey session persistence)\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Interface Definition\n  - Define `Store` interface with methods:\n    - `Ping(ctx) error`\n    - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n    - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n    - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n    - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error`\n    - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n    - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n    - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n    - `Close() error`\n  - Define `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Singleton Pattern\n  - Define `initStoreOnce sync.Once`\n  - Define `provider Store`\n  - Implement `Storage() Store` function\n  - Implement `initStore()` function\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Error Types\n  - Define error constants:\n    - `ErrNotFound`\n    - `ErrNilSandbox`\n    - `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n    - `ErrEmptySessionID`\n    - `ErrInvalidProvider`\n    - `ErrPasswordRequired`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Provider Type Constants\n  - Define constants:\n    - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n    - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 3: Redis Implementation - Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Configuration Function\n  - Implement `makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error)`\n  - Read `REDIS_ADDR` env var (required)\n  - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` env var\n  - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n  - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n  - Return `redisv9.Options{Addr, Password}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Struct Definition\n  - Define `redisStore struct` with fields:\n    - `cli *redisv9.Client`\n    - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n    - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n    - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n  - Implement `NewRedisStore(addr, password string) (*redisStore, error)`\n  - Create client, set key prefixes\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Implement helper function `sessionKey(sessionID string) string`\n  - Return `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 4: Redis Implementation - Core Methods\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` for redisStore\n  - Execute `cli.Ping(ctx)`\n  - Expect `PONG` response\n  - Return error if ping fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n  - Execute `cli.Get(ctx, key)`\n  - Handle `redis.Nil` вҶ’ return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Return sandbox and nil on success\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 1\n  - Validate: reject nil sandbox вҶ’ return `ErrNilSandbox`\n  - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt вҶ’ return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 2 (Pipeline)\n  - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n  - Execute `SETNX session:{id} <json>` (only create if not exists)\n  - Execute `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}`\n  - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}`\n  - Exec pipeline\n  - Return error if SETNX fails (session already exists) or any command fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore\n  - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n  - Execute `SET key value XX` (only if exists)\n  - Return error if key doesn't exist\n  - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs (expiry, last_activity remain unchanged)\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for redisStore - Pipeline\n  - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n  - Execute `DEL session:{id}`\n  - Execute `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n  - Execute `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n  - Exec pipeline\n  - Return error if any command fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 1\n  - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n  - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n  - Get list of session IDs from result\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.8** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 2\n  - For each sessionID, execute `GET session:{id}`\n  - Pipeline GET requests for efficiency\n  - Skip missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n  - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Return slice of sandboxes\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.9** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n  - Same logic as T4.7-T4.8 but use `session:last_activity` ZSET\n  - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.10** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for redisStore\n  - Validate: reject empty sessionID вҶ’ return `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n  - Check if key exists: `cli.Exists(ctx, key)`\n  - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T4.11** Implement `Close() error` for redisStore\n  - Execute `cli.Close()`\n  - Return error on failure\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 5: Valkey Implementation - Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Configuration Function\n  - Implement `makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error)`\n  - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` env var (required, comma-separated)\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` env var\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n  - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` env var (optional)\n  - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` env var (optional)\n  - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n  - Return `valkey.ClientOption` with InitAddress, Password, DisableCache, ForceSingleClient\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Struct Definition\n  - Define `valkeyStore struct` with fields:\n    - `cli valkey.Client`\n    - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n    - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n    - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n  - Implement `NewValkeyStore(addr, password string) (*valkeyStore, error)`\n  - Create client using `valkey.NewClient()`, set key prefixes\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 6: Valkey Implementation - Core Methods\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Implement `Ping(ctx) error` for valkeyStore\n  - Build command: `B().Ping().Build()`\n  - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n  - Expect `PONG` string response\n  - Return error if ping fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n  - Build command: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n  - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n  - Check `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp)` вҶ’ return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - Validation & JSON\n  - Validate: reject nil sandbox вҶ’ return `ErrNilSandbox`\n  - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt вҶ’ return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n  - Build commands:\n    - `B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` (SETNX)\n    - `B().Zadd().Key(expiryIndexKey).Score(float64(expiresAtUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n    - `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(nowUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n  - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n  - Check SETNX result: if 0, session already exists вҶ’ error\n  - Return error if any command fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore\n  - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n  - Check existence first: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n  - If not exists, return error\n  - Execute `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()`\n  - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n  - Build commands:\n    - `B().Del().Key(sessionKey(sessionID)).Build()`\n    - `B().Zrem().Key(expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n    - `B().Zrem().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n  - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n  - Return error if any command fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n  - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n  - Build command: `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n  - Execute and get session IDs\n  - Build MGET command: `B().Mget().Keys(sessionKeys...).Build()`\n  - Skip missing keys (IsValkeyNil)\n  - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.8** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n  - Same logic as T6.7 but use `lastActivityIndexKey`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.9** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for valkeyStore\n  - Validate: reject empty sessionID\n  - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n  - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n  - Check existence: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n  - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Build command: `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(at.Unix())).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n  - Execute command\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T6.10** Implement `Close() error` for valkeyStore\n  - Execute `cli.Close()`\n  - Return error on failure\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 7: initStore Implementation\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Implement `initStore()` function - Provider Selection\n  - Read `STORE_TYPE` env var\n  - If \"redis\", call `initRedisStore()`\n  - If \"valkey\", call `initValkeyStore()`\n  - If empty or other, return `ErrInvalidProvider`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Implement `initRedisStore()` helper\n  - Call `makeRedisOptions()`\n  - Create Redis client: `redisv9.NewClient(opts)`\n  - Set provider to `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Implement `initValkeyStore()` helper\n  - Call `makeValkeyOptions()`\n  - Create Valkey client: `valkey.NewClient(opts)`\n  - Set provider to `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n\n### Phase 8: Unit Tests - Redis Store\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` - Test Setup\n  - Create `setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore` helper\n  - Use `miniredis.RunT(t)` for in-memory Redis\n  - Create `makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo` helper\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Test `Ping()` for redisStore\n  - Test successful ping returns nil\n  - Test ping on closed client returns error\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisPing`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` for redisStore\n  - Test get existing session returns sandbox\n  - Test get non-existing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n  - Test deserialization correctness\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisGet`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4** Test `StoreSandbox()` for redisStore - Success & Validation\n  - Test successful store creates session, ZSET entries\n  - Test reject nil sandbox returns `ErrNilSandbox`\n  - Test reject zero ExpiresAt returns `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisStore`\n\n- [ ] **T8.5** Test `StoreSandbox()` for redisStore - Duplicate Prevention\n  - Test duplicate store fails (SETNX behavior)\n  - Verify session not overwritten\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisStoreDuplicate`\n\n- [ ] **T8.6** Test `UpdateSandbox()` for redisStore\n  - Test update existing session succeeds\n  - Test update non-existing session fails\n  - Test ZSETs remain unchanged after update\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisUpdate`\n\n- [ ] **T8.7** Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` for redisStore\n  - Test delete removes session key and ZSET members\n  - Test delete non-existing session succeeds (DEL returns 0)\n  - Verify ZSET members removed\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisDelete`\n\n- [ ] **T8.8** Test `ListExpiredSandboxes()` for redisStore\n  - Test list returns sessions before expiry time\n  - Test limit parameter respected\n  - Test skip orphan ZSET members (missing session keys)\n  - Test limit вүӨ 0 returns nil\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisListExpired`\n\n- [ ] **T8.9** Test `ListInactiveSandboxes()` for redisStore\n  - Test list returns sessions before activity time\n  - Test limit parameter respected\n  - Test skip orphan ZSET members\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisListInactive`\n\n- [ ] **T8.10** Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` for redisStore\n  - Test update activity succeeds\n  - Test reject empty sessionID returns `ErrEmptySessionID`\n  - Test update non-existing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n  - Test zero time uses `time.Now()`\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisUpdateActivity`\n\n- [ ] **T8.11** Test `Close()` for redisStore\n  - Test close succeeds\n  - Test operations fail after close\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestRedisClose`\n\n### Phase 9: Unit Tests - Valkey Store (Mock-based)\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` - Mock Setup\n  - Create mock valkey.Client interface\n  - Create test helpers for mocking responses\n  - Create `setupTestValkeyStore(t *testing.T) *valkeyStore` helper\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n\n- [ ] **T9.2** Test `Ping()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test successful ping returns nil\n  - Test ping failure returns error\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyPing`\n\n- [ ] **T9.3** Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test get existing session returns sandbox\n  - Test get non-existing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n  - Test `IsValkeyNil` handling\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyGet`\n\n- [ ] **T9.4** Test `StoreSandbox()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test successful store with DoMulti\n  - Test validation errors\n  - Test duplicate prevention (SETNX returns 0)\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyStore`\n\n- [ ] **T9.5** Test `UpdateSandbox()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test update existing session\n  - Test update non-existing session fails\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyUpdate`\n\n- [ ] **T9.6** Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test delete removes all keys/ZSET members\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyDelete`\n\n- [ ] **T9.7** Test `ListExpiredSandboxes()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test ZRANGEBYSCORE and MGET\n  - Test limit and orphan handling\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyListExpired`\n\n- [ ] **T9.8** Test `ListInactiveSandboxes()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test activity ZSET query\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyListInactive`\n\n- [ ] **T9.9** Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test existence check and ZADD\n  - Test validation errors\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyUpdateActivity`\n\n- [ ] **T9.10** Test `Close()` for valkeyStore (mock)\n  - Test close succeeds\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestValkeyClose`\n\n### Phase 10: Unit Tests - Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Test `makeRedisOptions()` - Success\n  - Test with valid env vars\n  - Test password optional when PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestMakeRedisOptions`\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Test `makeRedisOptions()` - Errors\n  - Test missing REDIS_ADDR returns error\n  - Test missing password when required returns `ErrPasswordRequired`\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestMakeRedisOptions`\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Test `makeValkeyOptions()` - Success\n  - Test with comma-separated addresses\n  - Test optional flags parsed correctly\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestMakeValkeyOptions`\n\n- [ ] **T10.4** Test `makeValkeyOptions()` - Errors\n  - Test missing VALKEY_ADDR returns error\n  - Test missing password when required returns `ErrPasswordRequired`\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestMakeValkeyOptions`\n\n- [ ] **T10.5** Test `initStore()` - Provider Selection\n  - Test STORE_TYPE=redis initializes redisStore\n  - Test STORE_TYPE=valkey initializes valkeyStore\n  - Test invalid/empty STORE_TYPE returns `ErrInvalidProvider`\n  - Test `Storage()` returns singleton\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run TestInitStore`\n\n### Phase 11: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Create `pkg/store/store_integration_test.go`\n  - Mark tests with `testing.Short()` skip\n  - Test against real Redis/Valkey if available\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run Integration`\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Test Redis integration - End-to-end\n  - Test create вҶ’ get вҶ’ update вҶ’ delete flow\n  - Test ZSET indexing correctness\n  - Test expiry and activity queries\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run IntegrationRedis`\n\n- [ ] **T11.3** Test Valkey integration - End-to-end\n  - Test full lifecycle operations\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -run IntegrationValkey`\n\n### Phase 12: Validation & Quality\n\n- [ ] **T12.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/store/...`\n  - Fix any issues reported\n  - Verify: `go vet ./pkg/store/...`\n\n- [ ] **T12.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/store/...`\n  - Fix any linting issues\n  - Verify: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/store/...`\n\n- [ ] **T12.3** Run `go mod tidy`\n  - Clean up dependencies\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n\n- [ ] **T12.4** Verify build\n  - Run: `go build ./pkg/store/...`\n  - Ensure no build errors\n\n- [ ] **T12.5** Verify test coverage\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -cover`\n  - Ensure coverage вүҘ 80%\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out`\n\n- [ ] **T12.6** Verify all tests pass\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -race`\n  - Ensure all tests pass with race detector\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1.1-T1.4 (Dependencies Setup)\n    вҶ“\nT2.1-T2.5 (Interface & Types)\n    вҶ“\nT3.1-T3.3 (Redis C